PROBLEM 2.4
Arrange the following functions in order of increasing
growth rate, with g(n) following f(n) in your list if and only if
f(n)=O(g(n)).

a) n^2 . log2 n
b) 2^n
c) 2^2^n
d) n^log2 n
e) n^2

lets do small example
n=4
a. 4^2 . log2 4 -> 16 . 2 = 32
b. 2^4 = 16
c. 2^2^n -> 2^2^4 -> 2^16 = 65536
d. 4^log2 4 -> 4^2 -> 16
e. 4^2 -> 16

lets do large example
n=100
a. 100^2 . log2 . 100 -> 301,030
b. 2^100 = 1.2676506e+30
c. 2^2^100 -> extremely large
d. 100^log2 100 -> 1.9396009e+13
e. 100^2 -> 10000

from slowest to fastest
e > a > d > b > c


